I"ˆ6<h1 class="post-title" itemprop="name headline">Tandem Riboswitches</h1>
<p>Tandem riboswitches refer to the arrangement of aptamers or complete riboswitches in tandem, creating RNA systems with more complex gene regulatory functions. Various types of independent tandem riboswitches have been identified. We present three categories for discussing multi-ligand sensing and regulation by riboswitches and tandem riboswitches: ‚ÄòSingle riboswitch sensing multiple ligand molecules‚Äô,‚ÄôTandem riboswitches sensing identical ligands‚Äô, and ‚ÄòTandem riboswitches sensing multiple ligands‚Äô.
<br /><br /></p>

